        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Various parts of this +2 <em>resilient half plate</em> are forged into the shape of a lion's head. The golden lion heads grant you a commanding presence and seem to actively growl at your enemies, granting you a +2 item bonus to Intimidation.</p>\n<p>The lions on the armor work in tandem with the lion on a <em>lion's shield</em>. If you critically hit with the <em>lion's shield</em> using Lion Bite, the lions on the armor roar in support of the shield, causing the target of the shield's Strike to become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Activateâ€”Roar of the Pride</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> (concentrate)</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The lions on your armor roar, attempting to cow your enemies. Attempt a check to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Demoralize] each enemy within 30 feet of you. On a critical success, the target is also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Fleeing] for 1 round.</p>"
